    "instruction": "Using trace.csv, restrict to cmdb_id in [checkoutservice, currencyservice, emailservice, productcatalogservice, recommendationservice]. For each unique (cmdb_id, trace_name) compute global P95 and P5 over the full available series (do NOT filter by incident window for threshold). Then filter trace rows to the incident window 2024-01-19 22:30:43 UTC to 2024-01-19 23:00:43 UTC and for each pair produce one compact aggregate row with: cmdb_id, trace_name, total_count_all, p95, p5, count_in_window, count_ge_p95_in_window, earliest_timestamp_ge_p95_in_window (UTC or null), count_le_p5_in_window, earliest_timestamp_le_p5_in_window (UTC or null), max_value_in_window, min_value_in_window. Only output rows where count_in_window>0 and (count_ge_p95_in_window>0 or count_le_p5_in_window>0). Limit output to top 20 rows ordered by count_ge_p95_in_window desc then count_le_p5_in_window desc then count_in_window desc. Keep output compact (one row per pair)."
