    "instruction": "Focus on cmdb_id = 'recommendationservice' and the incident window 2024-01-19 22:30:43 UTC to 2024-01-19 23:00:43 UTC. Produce three compact outputs (limit 20 rows each):\n1) Metric anomaly runs: For each recommendationservice (kpi_name) where any anomalies exist (based on global P95/P5 computed over the full series), list rows with fields: kpi_name, anomaly_type ('high' or 'low'), run_start_utc, run_end_utc, run_length, max_value_in_run, min_value_in_run, severity_ratio (max/p95 for 'high' or p5/min for 'low'). Only include runs with run_length>=2. Order by severity_ratio desc then run_length desc.\n2) Trace duration anomalies: For trace_name values containing 'duration_mean' or 'duration_p95' for recommendationservice, compute global P95 (full series) and report aggregates for the incident window: trace_name, p95, p5, count_in_window, count_ge_p95_in_window, earliest_timestamp_ge_p95_in_window (UTC or null), max_value_in_window, min_value_in_window, severity_ratio (max/p95; null if p95==0). Only include pairs where count_ge_p95_in_window>0. Order by severity_ratio desc.\n3) Log anomalies: For recommendationservice log_name entries (from log.csv), compute global P95/P5 (full series) and report for the incident window: log_name, p95, p5, count_in_window, count_ge_p95_in_window, earliest_timestamp_ge_p95_in_window (UTC or null), count_le_p5_in_window, earliest_timestamp_le_p5_in_window (UTC or null), max_value_in_window, min_value_in_window. Only include rows where count_in_window>0 and (count_ge_p95_in_window>0 or count_le_p5_in_window>0). Order by count_ge_p95_in_window desc then count_le_p5_in_window desc.\nReturn the three compact tables so we can finalize the root-cause decision."
